Nollywood veteran actress, Patience Oseni is dead. The actress was said to have died on Monday, February 17, 2020, in Calabar, Cross River State, following a battle with stroke and weight. She was said to have relocated to Calabar with hope that her daughter would take adequate care of her, unfortunately, the latter was also ill at the same time. According to National President of Actors Guild of Nigeria (AGN), Emeka Rollas who announced her demise, he said; “With deep sense of sorrow but with total submission to the will of Almighty God, we announce the passing unto eternal glory of Patience Oseni, veteran Actress and member of the Actors Guild of Nigeria.” For those who don’t know, Patience Oseni began her acting career in 1995 with her first movie; ‘Deadly Passion’. She rose to stardom through the movie; ‘End Of The Wicked’ and Super Story series; ‘Heat Of The Moment’. She was a member of the Actors Guild of Nigeria (AGN).